{
  "texts": [
    "A prominent example of GenAI is the Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), introduced by Goodfellow et al. in 2014 [23,24].",
    "GANs have demonstrated effectiveness in various medical applications, including medical image analysis [25][26][27][28] and disease progression modeling [29,30].",
    "In the context of aging research, GenAI techniques like GANs have shown promise in several areas.",
    "They have facilitated the development of biomarkers and early geroprotective interventions [31,32], advanced understanding of age-related changes, and improved dataset balance for training more accurate predictive models.",
    "For instance, Campello et al. (2022) used GANs to synthesize aged and rejuvenated cardiac images from cross-sectional data, modeling realistic age-related changes in the heart [33]."
  ]
}